    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content </head>
      <p>Three notebooks comprising 300 manuscript pages of arithmetic, surveying, and
                commercial accounting methods and calculations. The first notebook (Harmanus
                Hoagland, 1787-1791) contains all the rules of basic mathematics and advanced
                problem solving. It also includes sections devoted to commercial calculations. The
                second notebook (ca. 1800) is devoted to the science of surveying and map making and
                is an advanced text. The third notebook (Lucas Hoagland, ca. 1825) is devoted to
                problem solving for commercial transactions.</p>
    </scopecontent>
